    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nVirtual text with left gravity shown on two lines after pasting above:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/35768171/a734b112-b4f5-43dc-901e-b4a50f7509ab\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Source the following file:\r\n```vim\r\ncall setline(1, ['aaa', 'bbb', 'ccc', 'ddd'])\r\nlet ns = nvim_create_namespace('')\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, #{virt_text: [['foo']], right_gravity: v:false})\r\n```\r\n3. Press `yyp`\r\n4. Virtual text is shown on both line 2 and line 3\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nVirtual text is only shown on one line. After pressing `<C-L>` it is shown on line 2, which may or may not be the expected behavior.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-2294+gc0b99bb1de \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.31.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
